Module testing
Package faultmodel.mgf.pmgfdatastructure

Class PMGFResult

java.lang.Object
faultmodel.mgf.pmgfdatastructure.PMGFResult
public class PMGFResult extends Object
Data structure use to store the result of PMGF test.

It uses Node objects to construct a graph which is essentially used to store the result.

Author:
AKASH

  • Method Details

    • set

      public void set(int gateNo, int controlNo, int tVecNo) throws PMGFException
      Links a particular control input of a particular gate with a particular test vector.

      Creates a link from a control node to a test vector node as well as from that test vector node to that particular control node to show that a particular control is tested by a particular test vector.

      Each control must be associated with a gate and thus three parameters are required.

      Parameters:
      gateNo - Gate number of the circuit.
      controlNo - Control point number of the gate.
      tVecNo - Test vector number of the test set.
      Throws:
      PMGFException

    • setForNoControl

      public void setForNoControl(int gateNo, int tVecNo) throws PMGFException
      It is similar to the set method except it is used for CNOT gates.

      CNOT gate do not have any control input line, thus this method do not take any control number.

      Parameters:
      gateNo - Gate number of the circuit.
      tVecNo - Test vector number of the test set.
      Throws:
      PMGFException

    • gateToGateCtrlTVecs

      public Map<Integer,int[]> gateToGateCtrlTVecs(int gateNo) throws PMGFException
      Provided with the gate number, it returns a Map containing information about which gate control line is tested by which test vectors.
      Parameters:
      gateNo - Gate number of the circuit.
      Returns:
      Map whose key represents the control number and value represents the list of test vectors which tests the control of the gate
      Throws:
      PMGFException

    • tVecToGateGateCtrl

      public Map<Integer,Integer> tVecToGateGateCtrl(int tVecNo) throws PMGFException
      Provided with the test vector number, it returns a Map containing information about which gates and their controls are tested by the test vector.
      Parameters:
      tVecNo - Test vector number of the test set.
      Returns:
      Map whose keys are the gate numbers and values are the control numbers.
      Throws:
      PMGFException

    • isCircuitTested

      public boolean isCircuitTested()
      Returns true if the entire circuit is tested otherwise returns false.

      True if all the controls of all the gates are tested by at least one test vector.

      Returns:
      true if the circuit is tested otherwise false.
